deck: A rifle capable of killing demons.
description:
The Ace of Winchesters is a magical rifle made to kill Demons. It was made by a mystic occultist who was in the Texas Rangers. It is made from "halo-steel and hades-gems, bound in the ivory of saints".

The rifle fell into the possession of a man named Zeerke and was sought by collector Jerry O'Flynn, who hired John Constantine and Brendan Finn to retrieve the rifle. Zeerke initially demanded for a sum of £500,000 in exchange for the rifle until he later doubled his asking price, which forced Constantine and Finn to stealing it. O'Flynn took ownership of the Ace of Winchesters and sold it for a hefty profit.

The Ace of Winchesters ended up on display in the Gotham City Museum of Antiquities. The demon Mawzir hired Catwoman to stealing the rifle for him in order to prevent it from falling into the hands of his nemesis Tommy Monaghan and using it against him. Monaghan and his associates, along with Catwoman and Etrigan, managed to retrieve the rifle and kill Mawzir.

Other media appearance

The Ace of Winchesters appeared in the short lived Constantine tv series in the episodies "The devil's vynil" and "Waitnig for the man".

The Ace of Winchesters most probably inspired The Colt, an Old-West-made, demon-killing pistol seen in the TV series Supernatural. The show's creator, Eric Kripke, claims to be a fan of Hellblazer and even based the look of the angel Castiel on John Constantine. Kripke's main characters Sam and Dean also have Winchester for their surnames.
name: Ace of Winchesters

description:
Origin

Planet X was created by the United State Air Force in 1960. It is a satellite that orbits the earth with all known weather equipment, Geiger counters and, a missile guidance system. It also takes highly magnified television pictures of any potential military threat around the world. As a spy satellite it drew the attention of enemy nations and was a attacked several times with missiles but Captain Atom deflected all the attacks. As none of the nations knew how their missiles were destroyed it was thought that the satellite had defense systems. This kept the satellite safe from enemy attacks.

Creation

Planet X was created by Joe Gill and, Steve Ditko.

The Mecha Class exo-armor was based upon the original Manowar armor of Shanhara. Created by the greatest minds on the planet earth using scraps of the original X-O Manowar's own substance. These armors came in one of two varieties which were the unmanned humanoid armor drones piloted by the central intelligence of a runaway system program created by P.R.S. and the Colossal mecha suits piloted by one or more experienced combatants.

Giant Mecha Version

Charged Ionic Weaponry

Individual Manowar armors made by various countries produced an energized tool or armament reminiscent to their native countries archaic symbolism. The weapon produced also depends on the pilots own desires as Rai utilized the ancient colossus to generate an energy Katana.

Remote Anatomical Control

The Mechawar could detach and operate independently of the bodily whole when willed too by a pilot.

Mecha Class Manowars all come equipped with two silos of discharged ballistic packages fired from its chest region.

deck: The exo-skeletal armor that the Controller wears that enables him to perform superhuman feats. It also allows him to move in general as without it the Controller is paralyzed.
description:
The Controller's power suit is an exoskeleton that has been micro-surgically grafted to his body. It provides mobility and enhanced physical attributes in geometric progression to the number of victims wearing slave discs. Among these attributes are the following:

Strength: Under normal circumstances the suit allows the Controller to lift approximately one ton of weight, with all the implications thereof. eg: The Controller can easily beat a normal human to death, throw him into walls, crush metal and stone, etc. At full power the Controller has been known to lift up to 50 tons of weight. The strength associated with this has impressed even Captain Marvel, who once described the Controller's punches as almost enough to decapitate him.

Durability: As an exoskeleton, the power suit provides the Controller with substantial amounts of added durability. While not bulletproof, the suit allows the Controller to brush off many attacks that a normal human would not be able to withstand. In particular, he is strong against blunt force and impact damage. By draining more slave discs, he can enhance this ability, notably in order to withstand full blast damage from Iron Man.

Stamina: The suit is significantly more efficient than normal human musculature, allowing the Controller to work at maximum output for several hours before experiencing fatigue.

Mental Blast: The headpiece of the suit can project a bolts of pure energy, likely converted from the harvested mental energy of his victims.

Flight: While the Controller has occasionally exhibited the ability to levitate, his primary means of flight are a pair of jet-boots built into the power suit. It is estimated that he can fly up to 10 mph.
name: Controller's Armor
